quran[57]{c,v,t}:
  73,20,"Thy Lord knows that thou keepest vigil nearly two-thirds of the night, or a half of it, or a third of it, and a party of those with thee; and God determines the night and the day. He knows that you will not number it, and He has turned towards you. Therefore recite of the Koran so much as is feasible. He knows that some of you are sick, and others journeying in the land, seeking the bounty of God, and others fighting in the way of God. So recite of it so much as is feasible. And perform the prayer, and pay the alms, and lend to God a good loan. Whatever good you shall forward to your souls' account, you shall find it with God as better, and mightier a wage. And ask God's forgiveness; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate"
  74,1,O thou shrouded in thy mantle
  74,2,"arise, and warn"
  74,3,Thy Lord magnify
  74,4,thy robes purify
  74,5,and defilement flee
  74,6,"Give not, thinking to gain greater"
  74,7,and be patient unto thy Lord
  74,8,For when the Trump is sounded
  74,9,that day will be a harsh day
  74,10,for the unbelievers not easy
  74,11,Leave Me with him whom I created alone
  74,12,and appointed for him ample wealth
  74,13,and sons standing before him
  74,14,and made all things smooth for him
  74,15,then he is eager that I should do more
  74,16,Nay! He is forward unto Our signs
  74,17,and I shall constrain him to a hard ascent
  74,18,"Lo! He reflected, and determined"
  74,19,"death seize him, how he determined"
  74,20,"Again, death seize him, how he determined"
  74,21,Then he beheld
  74,22,"then he frowned, and scowled"
  74,23,"then he retreated, and waxed proud"
  74,24,"He said, 'This is naught but a trumped-up sorcery"
  74,25,this is nothing but mortal speech
  74,26,I shall surely roast him in Sakar
  74,27,and what will teach thee what is Sakar
  74,28,"It spares not, neither leaves alone"
  74,29,scorching the flesh
  74,30,over it are nineteen
  74,31,"We have appointed only angels to be masters of the Fire, and their number We have appointed only as a trial for the unbelievers, that those who were given the Book may have certainty, and that those who believe may increase in belief, and that those who were given the Book and those who believe may not be in-doubt, and that those in whose hearts there is sickness, and the unbelievers, may say, 'What did God intend by this as a similitude?' So God leads astray whomsoever He will, and He guides whomsoever He will; and none knows the hosts of thy Lord but He. And it is naught but a Reminder to mortals"
  74,32,Nay! By the moon
  74,33,and the night when it retreats
  74,34,and the dawn when it is white
  74,35,surely it is one of the greatest things
  74,36,as a warner to mortals
  74,37,to whoever of you desires to go forward or lag behind
  74,38,Every soul shall be pledged for what it has earned
  74,39,save the Companions of the Right
  74,40,in Gardens they will question
  74,41,concerning the sinners
  74,42,What thrusted you into Sakar
  74,43,"They shall say, 'We were not of those who prayed, and"
  74,44,we fed not the needy
  74,45,and we plunged along with the plungers
  74,46,and we cried lies to the Day of Doom
  74,47,till the Certain came to us
  74,48,Then the intercession of the intercessors shall not profit them
  74,49,"What ails them, that they turn away from the Reminder"
  74,50,as if they were startled asses
  74,51,fleeing -- before a lion
  74,52,"Nay, every man of them desires to be -- given -- scrolls unrolled"
  74,53,No indeed; but they do not fear the Hereafter
  74,54,No indeed; surely it is a Reminder
  74,55,so whoever wills shall remember it
  74,56,"And they will not remember, except that God wills; He is worthy to be feared, -- worthy to forgive"